Author:  FORSTER
Vol / Page:  2/267
Edition:
Quote:  The Scenery of the country was bold & worthy of the Pencil of a <i>Salvator Rosa</i>, all the Sides of hills were steep, rocky, & on all the little slopes & small terrasses or Settlements covered with fine shrubs, of various kinds; we saw here a great many <i>Palmtrees,</i> [ed. fn Cordyline sp.] of the same kind as had been found on April Ye 24th.
